
[1]commination

   COMMINATION, n.

   1. A threat or threatening; a denunciation of punishment or vengeance.

   2. The recital of Gods threatenings on stated days; an office in the
   Liturgy of the Church of England, appointed to be read on Ash Wednesday
   or on the first day of Lent.
